messages.message: Did JPMC use model service at all? If so, there are backward incompatible changes there.
I believe all changes are captured in our release notes (https://instabase.com/docs/releasenotes/) as well

On the platform side, there shouldn’t be any changes to structure (request/response) of the APIs themselves, but a bunch of validation was added to bolster up the correctness of file-system and mount APIs (e.g. catching invalid path names or formats, invalid offsets, catching malformed mount configs, etc).
Thanks @lydia - I did go through the release notes and nothing stood out, but i’ll re-review and make sure we account for those. JPMC are not using Model Service as far as i’m aware
